Class GameEngine

java.lang.Object
GameEngine
public class GameEngine
extends java.lang.Object
This class is part of the RPandaScape application. RPandaScape is a very simple, text based adventure game. This class creates all rooms, creates the parser and starts the game. It also evaluates and executes the commands that the parser returns.
Version:
1.0 (Jan 2003) DB edited (2019) edited (2021)
Author:
Michael Kolling and David J. Barnes and Elie DUBOUX

      public void interpretCommand​(java.lang.String pCommandLine)
      Given a command, process (that is: execute) the command. If this command ends the game, true is returned, otherwise false is returned.
      Parameters:
      pCommandLine - The line typed by the player

    • goRoom

      private void goRoom​(Command pCommand)
      Try to go to one direction. If there is an exit, enter the new room, otherwise print an error message. Exemple : go 'direction' with: 'direction' -> one of the directions (north,south,east...)
      Parameters:
      pCommand - The command typed by the player.

    • eat

      private void eat​(Command pCommand)
      Do a specific action when the caracter eat an item. Exemple : > eat 'Item' with : 'Item' -> The name of the Item
      Parameters:
      pCommand - The command typed by the user. It contains the item to eat.

    • look

      private void look​(Command pCommand)
      Print the description of the room and it's exits if nothing is typed after. If the thing typed after is an item, print the desciption of the item. Exemple : > look or > look 'Item' with : 'Item' The name of the item
      Parameters:
      pCommand - The command typed by the player.

    • quit

      private void quit​(Command pCommand)
      Quit the games. Cannot have a second word.
      Parameters:
      pCommand - The command typed by the player.

    • take

      private void take​(Command pCommand)
      The player take an item X many time if present in the room. Exemple : >take 'Item' X or >take 'Item' with : 'Item' -> the name of the item X -> the number of time
      Parameters:
      pCommand - The command typed by the player.

    • drop

      private void drop​(Command pCommand)
      The player drop an item he has X many times if present in the players'inventory. Exemple : >drop 'Item' X or >drop 'Item' with : 'Item' -> the name of the item X -> the number of time
      Parameters:
      pCommand - The command typed by the player.

      Parameters:
      pCommand - The comand typed by the player.
